<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="93" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="93">
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. bipinnatum" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" rank="species" species="bipinnatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">A. bipinnatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. christensenianum" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" rank="species" species="christensenianum">
A. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
christensenianum
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.15281/jplantres1887.38.87" author="Koidzumi, G" journalOrPublisher="The Botanical Magazine" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" pagination="87 - 113" refId="B14" refString="Koidzumi, G, 1924. Contributiones and Cognitionem Florae Asiae Orientalis. The Botanical Magazine 38: 87 - 113, DOI: https://doi.org/10.15281/jplantres1887.38.87" title="Contributiones and Cognitionem Florae Asiae Orientalis." url="https://doi.org/10.15281/jplantres1887.38.87" volume="38" year="1924">Koidzumi 1924</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.15281/jplantres1887.44.7" author="Nakai, T" journalOrPublisher="The Botanical Magazine" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" pagination="7 - 40" refId="B17" refString="Nakai, T, 1930. Notulae ad planta Japoniae &amp; Koreae XXXVIII. The Botanical Magazine 44 (517): 7 - 40, DOI: https://doi.org/10.15281/jplantres1887.44.7" title="Notulae ad planta Japoniae &amp; Koreae XXXVIII." url="https://doi.org/10.15281/jplantres1887.44.7" volume="44" year="1930">Nakai 1930</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Kato, M" journalOrPublisher="Acta Phytotaxonomica et Geobotanica" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" pagination="101 - 118" refId="B13" refString="Kato, M, 1979. Taxonomic study of the genus Cornopteris (Athyriaceae). Acta Phytotaxonomica et Geobotanica 30: 101 - 118" title="Taxonomic study of the genus Cornopteris (Athyriaceae)." volume="30" year="1979">Kato 1979</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Serizawa, S" journalOrPublisher="Shokubutsu Kenkyu Zasshi" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" pagination="193 - 199" refId="B22" refString="Serizawa, S, 1981. Taxonomical notes on Asian ferns (7). Shokubutsu Kenkyu Zasshi 56: 193 - 199" title="Taxonomical notes on Asian ferns (7)." volume="56" year="1981">Serizawa 1981</bibRefCitation>
) as it has serrated pinnae and exindusiate sori. However, 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. bipinnatum" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" rank="species" species="bipinnatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">A. bipinnatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has more short stipes (10-20 cm long), smaller blades (20-40 cm 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
14-20 cm), 2-pinnate pinnae in the middle of the blades, and fronds with dark green adaxial surfaces. In contrast, 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. christensenianum" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" rank="species" species="christensenianum">
A. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
christensenianum
</taxonomicName>
has longer stipes (25-40 cm long), larger blades (30-60 cm 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
25-40 cm), 2-pinnate pinnatifid pinnae in the middle of the blades, and fronds with light green adaxial surfaces.
</paragraph>
