<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="93" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Distribution and ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="93">
<taxonomicName authorityName="K. Hori" authorityYear="2020" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Athyriaceae" genus="Athyrium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Athyrium bipinnatum" order="Polypodiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bipinnatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Athyrium bipinnatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known from the western part of Honshu, Shikoku, and Kyushu in Japan (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Map showing the known distribution of Athyrium bipinnatum in Japan." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.148.51589.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/413892" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">5</figureCitation>
